What is Netcat or NC
it is utility is used for just about anything under the sun involving TCP,UDP or UNIX domain scokets

It can open TCP connections send UDP packets listen an arbitory TCP and UDP Ports
* Communicating Two Machines *

First check the Port Number are Listening or not

--> $netcat -v <hostname> port <port_no>
ex.
$netcat -v <hostname> port 22

[ how to check port are listening or not ]
--> $netstat -tunlp | grep port

[ If you want the Port Listien ]

--> $netcat <hostname> -l <port_number>

Then check other maching port are listening or not

-->$netcat <hostname> port <port_number>

--[ connection succeeded ]

Then you can communicate or chat with two machines.


